column2: We  had two heavy rainstorms the day before (07/04) both am + pm w/ wind and hail during the rainstorms.  Also had some holiday boat traffic.
Lake was still as glass.  Had random lite rains 36 hours before.
Partly sunny/cloudy; rained off + on 24-48 hours before; 5-7 MPH wind
Lake was still w/ no apparent wind.
Lake appeared so clean today (cleanest appearance yet)? 5 MPH wind; sunny
Sunny; 10 MPH winds; prior to yesterday it had been raining off and on for 5 days (lite and heavy).
6 MPH wind; no rain for 4 days;Painted turtles (6") swimming near surface in center of bay
temperature has been 82-92 degrees last 5 days; 2 pontoon boats out in same area as me
2-3 nights down in 30 degree temperatures last 10 days; rained/drizzled off and on for last 7 days - rained hard yesterday for 20 minutes w/ drizzle off and on all day
Dozens of Tree Swallows swarming in circular motion together above water where bay meets lake.  They each seemed to dip down to the water periodically to pick something up e.g. food?
5/16-5/22 rained 3-5" over 5 day period 5/16-5/22 rained 3-5" over 5 day period; cottonwoods dropping today again

Small- small debris moving underwater not usually seen.  I'm not sure if it's seeds from cottonwood trees or something under water?  The bay- shallower- seemed to be more clear than the deeper part of the lake?
morning after July 4th weekend traffic - pair of Loons on lake fishing
4"-6" of rain since 07/08/19.  High water levels.

2"-4" rain since 7/18/19 clarity reading; pair of Loons fishing near me; highest water level since moved here in 2013; many less frogs + toads than 2018 such as:  less Wood Frogs- Boreal Chorus Frogs- Spring Peeper- American Toad- Gray Tree Frog- Green Frogs- American Bullfrogs than last year's song surveys.
Temps have been much cooler the last few days; low 50's at nights as low as 50 degrees;
Pair of Loons fishing near me
1/2" rain earlier in day; pair of loons arrived to fish near me; battery for temperature died at 24' :)
Light rain the day before; temperature has been unseasonably cool the last 10-12 days; high 40s/low 50s at night

Rained off and on throughout previous day (9/9/19); temperature continued to be unseasonably cool both day and night  (last three weeks-high 40s/low 50s at night) up 'til today which was in the 60s last night and 70s today.
No wind - lake clear as glass
Swallows feeding on insects in middle of lake (swarming)
Very windy; micro vegetation moving thru water
Raining last 2-3 days; undercurrent (?) lite wind

Secchi data only; neglected to check batteries before leaving :(  This is the second year out of three where water clarity increases later in the season on Swede Lake?  First time this season that water was not murky.
Quiet w/ no wind; very clear; clearest it has been all year.
